The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                    Thursday , November 12 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Nov. 11 (PTI): Passengers travelling by the Duronto Express will be provided bedrolls if they want.           
	Passengers will be asked to indicate their requirement on the reservation slip. They will have to pay Rs 25 along with the fare for the facility. Blankets will also be provided to those who hold RAC tickets, the railway ministry has said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A chargesheet has been filed against a man for allegedly trying to extort money from sitarist Anoushka Shankar. Junaid Khan had allegedly hacked her email account and got some of her private photographs.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi Metro has raised the minimum fare from Rs 6 to Rs 8 while the maximum will be Rs 30 instead of Rs 22. The 10 per cent discount on smart cards will continue.                  
	 Burdwan: The assistant driver of the Howrah-Guwahati Kamrup Express was electrocuted by the trains overhead wire while he was looking into a snag in the engines cooling system. Basudev Haldar, 45, died instantly. The train left with another co-driver after a three-hour halt.                                                                                                                                                               
